<chapter subject="Chemistry" id="129" name="Polymers">
    <easy>
        <question>
            <text>Polymers are high molecular mass substances consisting of repeating units called ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Monomers</option><option id="B">Atoms</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Large molecules formed by joining monomers.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>The process of formation of polymers from monomers is called ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Polymerization</option><option id="B">Hydrolysis</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Involves chemical bonding of monomers.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Natural polymers are found in ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Plants and Animals</option><option id="B">Laboratories</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Example: Proteins, Cellulose, Starch, Rubber.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Synthethic polymers are ____ polymers.</text>
            <option id="A">Man-made</option><option id="B">Naturally occurring</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Prepared in industry e.g. Polythene, Nylon.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Nylon 6,6 is an example of a(n) ____ polymer.</text>
            <option id="A">Synthetic</option><option id="B">Natural</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>A type of polyamide fiber.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Semi-synthetic polymers are derived from ____ polymers by chemical modification.</text>
            <option id="A">Natural</option><option id="B">Synthetic</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Example: Cellulose acetate (Rayon).</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Linear polymers consist of long and ____ chains.</text>
            <option id="A">Straight</option><option id="B">Branched</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Example: PVC, High density polythene.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Branched chain polymers contain linear chains having some ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Branches</option><option id="B">Cross-links</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Example: Low density polythene.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Cross-linked polymers are also known as ____ polymers.</text>
            <option id="A">Network</option><option id="B">Linear</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Formed by bi-functional or tri-functional monomers.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Addition polymerization is also called ____ polymerization.</text>
            <option id="A">Chain-growth</option><option id="B">Step-growth</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Monomers add up without loss of small molecules.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Condensation polymerization is also called ____ polymerization.</text>
            <option id="A">Step-growth</option><option id="B">Chain-growth</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Small molecules like water/alcohol are eliminated.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Polythene is formed by polymerization of ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Ethene</option><option id="B">Propene</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Simplest addition polymer.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Low Density Polythene (LDP) is obtained under ____ pressure.</text>
            <option id="A">High (1000-2000 atm)</option><option id="B">Low (6-7 atm)</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Highly branched structure.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>High Density Polythene (HDP) is obtained using ____ catalysts.</text>
            <option id="A">Ziegler-Natta</option><option id="B">Iron</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Triethylaluminium and titanium tetrachloride.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Polypropene is a polymer of ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Propene</option><option id="B">Butene</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Used in ropes, toys, etc.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Teflon is chemically ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Polytetrafluoroethene (PTFE)</option><option id="B">Polyacrylonitrile</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Used as non-stick coating.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Orlon is a commercial fiber of ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Polyacrylonitrile (PAN)</option><option id="B">Polythene</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Uses acrylonitrile as monomer.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Natural rubber is a linear polymer of ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Isoprene (2-methyl-1,3-butadiene)</option><option id="B">Chloroprene</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>cis-polyisoprene.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Vulcanization of rubber involves heating it with ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Sulphur</option><option id="B">Iron</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>To improve physical properties like elasticity/hardness.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Neoprene is a synthetic rubber prepared from ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Chloroprene</option><option id="B">Isoprene</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>2-chloro-1,3-butadiene.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Buna-S is a copolymer of 1,3-butadiene and ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Styrene</option><option id="B">Acrylonitrile</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>SBR (Styrene Butadiene Rubber).</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Buna-N is a copolymer of 1,3-butadiene and ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Acrylonitrile</option><option id="B">Styrene</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Resistant to action of petrol/oil.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Terylene (Dacron) is a ____ polymer.</text>
            <option id="A">Polyester</option><option id="B">Polyamide</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Made from ethylene glycol and terephthalic acid.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Nylon 6 is prepared from ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Caprolactam</option><option id="B">Adipic acid</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Ring opening polymerization.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Bakelite is a ____ polymer.</text>
            <option id="A">Thermosetting</option><option id="B">Thermoplastic</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
