        <question>
            <text>Thermoplastics can be ____ on heating.</text>
            <option id="A">Repeatedly softened and reshaped</option><option id="B">Never reshaped</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Due to linear/slightly branched structure.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Elastomers are polymers with ____ intermolecular forces.</text>
            <option id="A">Weakest (e.g. rubber)</option><option id="B">Strongest</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Allows them to stretch and retract.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Fiber has ____ intermolecular forces like H-bonding.</text>
            <option id="A">Strongest</option><option id="B">Weakest</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Example: Nylon, Polyesters.</explanation></question>
